org.openntf.domino.events

Interface IDominoListener


  • public interface IDominoListener
    Author:
    nfreeman The OpenNTF Domino Listener interface, used to listen for certain events on an object that implements Base

    • Method Detail

      • eventHappened

        boolean eventHappened(IDominoEvent event)
        Method that fires code for the events the listener support.
        Parameters:
        event - IDominoEvent holding a source, a target and a payload. Its getEvent() method returns the EnumEvent
        Returns:
        boolean success or failure of running the code Example:
        The following code checks for and runs code for AFTER_CREATE_DOCUMENT and AFTER_UPDATE_DOCUMENT events public boolean eventHappened(IDominoEvent event) { try { if (event.getEvent().equals(Events.AFTER_CREATE_DOCUMENT)) { // Do something and return true if successful; } if (event.getEvent().equals(Events.AFTER_UPDATE_DOCUMENT)) { // Do something and return true if successful; } return false; // something went wrong, maybe an EnumEvent not implemented } catch (Exception e) { return false; } }
        Since:
        openntf.domino 3.0.0

      • getEventTypes

        List<EnumEvent> getEventTypes()
        The events this listener provides code to act upon.
        Returns:
        A List of EnumEvents the implementation supports. The current list of EnumEvents supported can be found in Database Example:
        The following code will define that AFTER_CREATE_DOCUMENT and AFTER_UPDATE_DOCUMENT events are supported by this Listener
        public List getEventTypes() { ArrayList eventList = new ArrayList(); eventList.add(Events.AFTER_CREATE_DOCUMENT); eventList.add(Events.AFTER_UPDATE_DOCUMENT); return eventList; }
        Since:
        openntf.domino 3.0.0
